DataElement.preferredDefinition: A nucleic acid molecule similar to DNA but containing ribose rather than deoxyribose. RNA is formed upon a DNA template. There are several classes of RNA molecules. They play crucial roles in protein synthesis and other cell activities. (MedicineNet.com):Analysis using microarray technology (e.g., cDNA arrays to see gene expression or protein microarrays to profile the pattern of proteins).:A short textual account; having provided a short account._The average cell intensity for the nine probe cells that compose the cross at the center of the antisense probe array.:A statistical calculation describing the central tendency of a set of numbers; used to interpret quantitative data._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is an Integer (32-bit two's complement).
